# Dashboard (React)

Create React App + TypeScript. UI: React Bootstrap + styled-components. State: Redux Toolkit + RTK Query.

## Structure

```
pages/        Route-level views (HomePage, DashboardPage, admin/*)
components/   Reusable UI (common/, subscriptions/, dashboard/)
constants/    Shared config (e.g. serverNav.ts for dashboard server shell)
store/        Redux slices + RTK Query API modules (store/api/)
types/        Shared interfaces (ISettings, IServer, User, …)
helpers/      Hooks, theme, Discord/Stripe utilities
```

## Server dashboard layout

Server-scoped routes (`/dashboard/:serverId/*`) use a shared shell:

- [`constants/serverNav.ts`](dashboard/src/constants/serverNav.ts) — grouped nav sections, item metadata (path, name, icon, description), and `getServerNavItem()`
- [`components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx`](dashboard/src/components/dashboard/server/ServerLayout.tsx) — sidebar + page header + outlet wrapper
- Desktop: sticky grouped sidebar; mobile: Offcanvas nav from header menu button
- Layout/nav tokens live in [`helpers/theme.ts`](dashboard/src/helpers/theme.ts) (`layout`, `nav`, `layout.padding`, `layout.breakpoints`)

Add or rename server sub-routes in `serverNav.ts` and `routes.tsx` together.

## Track page (Notification List)

[`TrackPage.tsx`](dashboard/src/pages/dashboard/server/TrackPage.tsx) layout order: alerts → search → tracked list card. Search is the primary action; page title comes from the server shell header, not a duplicate card header.

- Search card uses `#track-search` anchor and responsive stacked input on narrow widths (`ContentPanel` styles).
- Search results use green-accent styling (`entity-list--search`, "Search results" panel); tracked lists use gold-accent styling (`entity-list--tracked`, `tracked-entities-card`).
- When the list is empty, only `TrackEmptyState` is shown (no empty section headers). When partially filled, only non-empty entity sections render.
- Unsaved state is shown in a sticky `TrackSaveBar` at the bottom of the viewport; adding from search also triggers a save reminder toast.

